---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "reveal.js/dist/reveal.css";
import "reveal.js/dist/theme/white.css";
---

<Layout title="Web Tech Demos – Presentation">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Zalando+Sans+Expanded:wght@400;600;700&family=Zalando+Sans:wght@400;500;600&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
  </Fragment>
  <div class="reveal slides-light">
    <div class="slides">
      <section>
        <h1 class="slide-heading-lg">Product Design</h1>
        <p class="slide-body text-xl mt-4">by Ka‘a Kihe</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h1 class="slide-heading-lg">Nothing Else Like the Web as a Medium</h1>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="slide-heading-sm mb-8">The web is...</h2>
        <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-6">
          <p class="fragment slide-heading-lg">interactive</p>
          <p class="fragment slide-heading-lg">adaptive</p>
          <p class="fragment slide-heading-lg">invisible</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h1 class="slide-heading-lg">
          The <em>design</em> is <strong>not</strong> the <em>product</em>
        </h1>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h1 class="slide-heading-lg slide-heading-sentence">
          Some useful ways designers can work with developers
        </h1>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="slide-topic">Colors</h2>
        <ul class="slide-list">
          <li class="fragment">
            Include intent alongside names — primary, secondary, body, heading
          </li>
          <li class="fragment">
            Full scale 50–950 <a
              href="https://tailwindcss.com/docs/customizing-colors"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              class="slide-link">(Tailwind-style)</a
            > provides flexibility, constraints, and consistency.
          </li>
          <li class="fragment">
            Consider states for your colors - hover, active, focus, etc.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="slide-topic">Fonts</h2>
        <ul class="slide-list">
          <li class="fragment">
            Web-first options like Google Fonts are fast, free, and easy to
            adopt
          </li>
          <li class="fragment">
            Foundry fonts can add cost and complexity — worth it when branding
            needs it
          </li>
          <li class="fragment">
            Variable fonts provide a lot of flexibility and control.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="slide-topic">Images</h2>
        <ul class="slide-list">
          <li class="fragment">
            A single source makes life easier for everyone
          </li>
          <li class="fragment">
            <code>hero-bg-desktop.jpg</code> is clearer than <code
              >IMG_4829_final_v2.png</code
            >
          </li>
          <li class="fragment">
            Drafting <code>alt</code> when you export helps — you know the intent
            best
          </li>
          <li class="fragment">
            Optimize your images - know best practices about when to use JPG,
            PNG, GIF, SVG.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="slide-topic">Handoff document</h2>
        <ul class="slide-list">
          <li class="fragment">
            A page or two of notes — just enough to share context and reduce
            back-and-forth
          </li>
          <li class="fragment">
            Breakpoints, spacing, component variants, anything that isn’t
            obvious at a glance
          </li>
          <li class="fragment">
            Documentation is a gift to future-you and to the team
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="slide-topic">What tends to get in the way</h2>
        <ul class="slide-list slide-list--compact">
          <li class="fragment">
            <strong>PDFs</strong> — nice for review, but the source file has inspectable
            specs
          </li>
          <li class="fragment">
            <strong>1x-only exports</strong> — 2x or design specs help devs match
            intent
          </li>
          <li class="fragment">
            <strong>Assets in many places</strong> — one shared location saves a lot
            of hunting
          </li>
          <li class="fragment">
            <strong>Screenshots instead of the working file</strong> — view access
            lets devs pull exact values
          </li>
          <li class="fragment">
            <strong>Inconsistent naming</strong> — agreeing on <code
              >Button</code
            > vs <code>btn-primary</code> up front helps
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="slide-heading-sm mb-8">Some Demos for Ya</h2>
        <a
          href="/"
          class="slide-cta inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-xl border px-6 py-3 text-lg font-medium transition-colors"
        >
          See'em all
        </a>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script>
    // @ts-expect-error no types for reveal.js
    const { default: Reveal } = await import("reveal.js");

    Reveal.initialize({
      hash: true,
      transition: "slide",
      backgroundTransition: "fade",
      keyboard: true,
    });
  </script>
</Layout>

<style is:global>
  :root {
    --font-sans: "Zalando Sans", system-ui, sans-serif;
    --font-sans-expanded:
      "Zalando Sans Expanded", "Zalando Sans", system-ui, sans-serif;
  }
  .reveal {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    background-color: var(--color-slide-viewport);
  }
  .reveal .slides {
    background-color: var(--color-slide-bg);
    box-shadow: var(--color-slide-shadow);
    border-radius: 2rem;
  }
  .reveal .slides section {
    min-height: 100vh;
    padding-inline: 2rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
  }
  .reveal h1,
  .reveal h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-sans-expanded);
    text-transform: none;
    color: var(--color-slide-title);
  }
  .reveal .slide-heading-lg {
    font-family: var(--font-sans-expanded);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    text-align: center;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .reveal .slide-heading-sentence {
    text-transform: none;
  }
  .reveal .slide-heading-sm {
    font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 1.75rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-align: center;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .reveal .slide-body {
    color: var(--color-slide-body);
  }
  .reveal .slide-body-muted {
    color: var(--color-slide-body);
    opacity: 0.85;
  }
  .reveal .slide-cta {
    color: var(--color-slide-title);
    border-color: var(--color-slide-title);
    background-color: rgba(45, 50, 123, 0.08);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .reveal .slide-cta:hover {
    background-color: rgba(45, 50, 123, 0.15);
    border-color: var(--color-slide-title);
  }
  .reveal .slides section a {
    color: var(--color-slide-title);
  }
  .reveal .slide-link {
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 0.2em;
  }
  .reveal .slide-link:hover {
    opacity: 0.85;
  }
  .reveal .slide-topic {
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3.5vw, 2.25rem);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .reveal .slide-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .reveal .slide-list li {
    color: var(--color-slide-body);
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.25rem);
    line-height: 1.6;
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
  }
  .reveal .slide-list li::before {
    content: "–";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-slide-title);
  }
  .reveal .slide-list code {
    font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;
    font-size: 0.9em;
    background: rgba(45, 50, 123, 0.12);
    padding: 0.15em 0.4em;
    border-radius: 0.25rem;
  }
  .reveal .slide-list--compact li {
    font-size: clamp(0.9rem, 1.8vw, 1.1rem);
    padding: 0.35rem 0;
  }
</style>
